About

  • 2014-Present

    PhD, Mathematics

    Michigan State University,
    Expected Graduation: May 2020
    Thesis Advisor: Teena Gerhardt

  • Summer 2015

    Teaching Online/Hybrid Courses

    Trinity Christian College program on teaching online and hybrid courses. Created online course using Moodle, which included learning activities and resources using a variety of technology tools.

  • Summer 2014

    Cryptanalysis & Exploitation Services Intern (NSA)

    Adapted mathematical problem solving skills to real world problems. Granted a Top Secret//SCI (sensitive compartmented information) security clearance with a full-scope polygraph. Learned about aspects of com- putational number theory related to cryptography, including efficient algorithms, RSA, DiffieHellman, digital signature schemes, primality tests, threshold schemes, and random number generation.

  • Sept 2010-May 2014

    Calvin College

    BSc Mathematics (honors),
    BA French (honors)

  • Summer 2013

    Women in Mathematics Program

    A five-week intensive program for mathematically talented undergraduate women. Took courses and gave presentations in Symbolic Dynamical Systems, Wavelets and Fourier Analysis, Discrete Models in Biology, and Resampling and Simulation in Statistics.
